		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">David Addington</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:David_Addington.jpg" class="image" title="David Addington"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6a/David_Addington.jpg/180px-David_Addington.jpg" width="180" height="264" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:David_Addington.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
David Addington</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>David S. Addington</b> (b. <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1957-01-22"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="01-22"><a href="/wiki/January_22" title="January 22">January 22</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1957" title="1957">1957</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/Washington,_D.C." title="Washington, D.C.">Washington, D.C.</a>), was <a href="/wiki/Chief_of_Staff_to_the_Vice_President_of_the_United_States" title="Chief of Staff to the Vice President of the United States">chief of staff</a> and former legal <a href="/wiki/Counsel" title="Counsel">counsel</a> to former <a href="/wiki/Vice_President_of_the_United_States" title="Vice President of the United States">Vice President</a> <a href="/wiki/Dick_Cheney" title="Dick Cheney">Dick Cheney</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> He was appointed to replace <a href="/wiki/Lewis_Libby" title="Lewis Libby">I. Lewis "Scooter" Libby Jr.</a> as Cheney's chief of staff upon Libby's resignation after being indicted on charges of <a href="/wiki/Perjury" title="Perjury">perjury</a> and <a href="/wiki/Obstruction_of_justice" title="Obstruction of justice">obstruction of justice</a> on <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2005-10-28"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="10-28"><a href="/wiki/October_28" title="October 28">October 28</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2005" title="2005">2005</a></span>.<sup id="cite_ref-Olberman_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Olberman-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> He was described by <i><a href="/wiki/U.S._News_%26_World_Report" title="U.S. News &amp; World Report">U.S. News &amp; World Report</a></i> as "the most powerful man you've never heard of."<sup id="cite_ref-Ragavan_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Ragavan-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
